document_data.Notable broadsheets:
The following were popular Waterdavian broadsheets:
*''[[The Vigilant Citizen]]'', which was one of the most reputable broadsheets in the city.{{Cite digital book/Downshadow||4}}
*''[[The Blue Unicorn]]'', which reported paranormal events such as haunted mansions or undead hiding among the nobility.
*The ''[[Daily Luck]]'', a sheet aimed at gamblers.
*''[[Horkle's Gossip Cauldron]]'', whose style of writing was said to be profane and blunt to the point of rudeness.{{Cite dragon/411/Eye on the Realms: The Storm Bird|3-4}} 
*''[[The Mocking Minstrel]]'', one of the most read broadsheets in the city, known for its caustic and sarcastic tone.{{Cite digital book/Downshadow||2}}
*The ''[[North Wind]]'', which focused on nobility gossip and fashion.{{Cite organized play/LFR/Gilding a Noble|5,44}}
*The [[Merchant's Friend]]{{Cite digital book/Downshadow||11}}
*[[Halivar's Broadsheet]]
